  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180°C/ 160°C (fan)/ gas 4</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1646127093018-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1646127093018-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1646127093018-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1646127093018-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1646127093018-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chips are in the oven, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely grate your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Cut your<strong> red chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Add the <strong>grated ginger</strong>, <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>rice vinegar</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> to a pot with 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [180ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1646127225823-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1646127225823-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1646127225823-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1646127225823-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1646127225823-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the pot to a medium-high heat and once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook for 15-20 min or until it has reduced to a sticky, syrup like consistency – this is your <strong>homemade sweet chilli sauce</strong></p><p>While the chilli sauce is cooking, top, tail and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong>, then top, tail and slice your <strong>radishes</strong> (as finely as you can)</p><p>Add the <strong>grated carrot</strong> and <strong>sliced radishes</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>remaining rice vinegar </strong>and<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> and set aside – this is your <strong>pickled salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1646128026487-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1646128026487-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1646128026487-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1646128026487-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1646128026487-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain, then pat your<strong> jumbo prawns</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add a handful of <strong>flour</strong> to a bowl</p><p>Crack your <strong>egg[s]</strong> into a separate bowl and beat with a fork</p><p>Add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> to a separate bowl</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1646128032084-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1646128032084-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1646128032084-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1646128032084-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1646128032084-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Coat the<strong> jumbo prawns </strong>in the <strong>flour</strong>, tap off any excess, then add to the <strong>beaten egg </strong>and finally press into the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> firmly to evenly coat all over</p><p>Cut your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat and add the <strong>brioche halves</strong>, cut-side down, and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted, set aside until serving and reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1646128036245-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1646128036245-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1646128036245-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1646128036245-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1646128036245-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>When the chips are almost ready, return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> (enough to cover the base of the pan)</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>breaded jumbo prawns</strong> and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until golden and cooked through – these are your <strong>crispy jumbo prawns</strong></p><p>Tip: Do the prawns in batches if you need to so you don't overcrowd the pan!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1646128040638-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1646128040638-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1646128040638-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1646128040638-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1646128040638-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, strip your <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander </strong>roughly, including the stalks</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>and <strong>mint</strong> to the pickled salad<strong> </strong>and mix everything together – this is your <strong>fragrant pickled salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1646128045520-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1646128045520-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1646128045520-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1646128045520-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1646128045520-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Spread each<strong> toasted brioche base </strong>and <strong>lid </strong>with<strong> mayo</strong>,<strong> </strong>then<strong> </strong>add a dollop of <strong>homemade sweet chilli sauce </strong>to the base with the <strong>crispy jumbo prawns</strong>,<strong> </strong>some <strong>fragrant pickled salad </strong>and top with a <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>brioche lid </strong>– this is your <strong>jumbo prawn burger with homemade sweet chilli sauce</strong></p><p>Serve with the <strong>remaining fragrant pickled salad </strong>and <strong>chips</strong> to the side</p><p>Sprinkle your <strong>shichimi togarashi </strong>all over the chips and enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
